{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777057840205,"sessionID":"ses_23f1ad229ffeRkk07R6QDybS6x","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"background_output","callID":"call_DeCdBk1mu5n4wejtT6cFrtZU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"block":false,"full_session":false,"include_thinking":false,"include_tool_results":false,"message_limit":20,"since_message_id":"","task_id":"bg_b02a46b2","thinking_max_chars":2000,"timeout":1000},"output":"Task Result\n\nTask ID: bg_b02a46b2\nDescription: Explore workspace structure\nDuration: 53s\nSession ID: ses_23f1a6fa3ffeg8meYp5wxlcyK3\n\n---\n\nThe `D:\\agent_workspace` environment is a structured agentic ecosystem centered on a \"unified command surface\" (`mycli`) and a reusable \"capability library.\"\n\n### 1. Primary Architecture\n*   **`capability-library/mycli/`**: The main entry point. It uses a \"directory-as-package\" model.\n    *   **`agent-cli`**: Unified interface for calling agents (Claude, Codex, OpenCode). It tracks state (sessions, schedules, mounts) in its `state/` directory.\n    *   **`agent-workflow`**: Orchestrates complex, multi-step tasks.\n    *   **`skill-library`**: Provides a discovery and registration layer for atomic \"skills\" located in `capability-library/skill-library/`.\n*   **`AGENT_SYSTEM/`**: Contains the organizational \"logic\" of the workspace, including templates, channel definitions, and core system rules.\n*   **`AGENTS/`**: Houses specific agent instances or platform-level agent configurations.\n\n### 2. Task & Workflow Patterns\n*   **Unified Execution**: Agents should prefer `mycli agent-cli run` for single tasks and `mycli agent-workflow` for multi-step processes.\n*   **Session Tracking**: `agent-cli` maintains a history of runs and event streams in `capability-library/mycli/agent-cli/state/runs/`, allowing for session persistence and auditing.\n*   **Transient Work**: The `tmp/` directory is the mandatory workspace for any intermediate files or experimental projects not explicitly assigned to a permanent directory.\n\n### 3. Status & Configuration Mechanisms\n*   **`AGENT_WPRKSPACE.md`**: The authoritative guide for agents operating in this environment. It defines the \"No-Assumption\" policy and priority of `mycli` over native CLIs.\n*   **`openclaw.json`**: The global configuration file defining model providers (Kimi, GPT-5/Codex, Gemini), API keys, and default tool profiles.\n*   **`capability-library/mycli/agent-cli/registry.json`**: The active registry of mapped agents available to the unified CLI.\n*   **`capability-library/mycli/skill-library/registry.json`**: The index of all discovered `SKILL.md` contracts.\n\n### 4. Relevant Directories for Investigation\n*   **`capability-library/agent-system-rules/agent-workflow/`**: The implementation and rule-base for the workflow engine.\n*   **`capability-library/skill-library/`**: The actual source code and contracts for specialized capabilities (e.g., memory, browser automation).\n*   **`projects/`**: Where independent, heterogeneous work-products reside.","metadata":{"truncated":false,"task_id":"bg_b02a46b2","agent":"Sisyphus-Junior","category":"quick","description":"Explore workspace structure","sessionId":"ses_23f1a6fa3ffeg8meYp5wxlcyK3"},"title":"quick - Explore workspace structure","time":{"start":1777057840191,"end":1777057840204}},"id":"prt_dc0e6bb53002mVl2ArjRKaeAl3","sessionID":"ses_23f1ad229ffeRkk07R6QDybS6x","messageID":"msg_dc0e68ccb001g7eCFk3v7AC096"}}
